NAME
    gcloud compute networks switch-mode - switch the mode of a Google Compute
        Engine network

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud compute networks switch-mode NAME --mode=MODE [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (REMOVED) switch-mode has been removed. Please use
    --switch-to-custom-subnet-mode with gcloud compute networks update instead.

    gcloud compute networks switch-mode is used to change the mode of a
    network. Currently, only changing from auto to custom mode is supported.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     NAME
        The name of the network for which to switch mode.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --mode=MODE
        The target mode of the network. Only support "custom" now.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

EXAMPLES
    To switch NETWORK to custom subnet mode, run:

        $ gcloud compute networks switch-mode NETWORK --mode custom

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice.

